overview: The user initiated a comprehensive review of their sleep questionnaire
  application to verify adherence to the project's acceptance criteria. The
  assistant identified several critical missing features and systematically
  addressed them. Key implementations included integrating a 1-10 severity scale
  for tiredness, complete with safety warnings for high scores, and adding
  detection and detailed reporting for COMISA (Comorbid Insomnia and Sleep
  Apnea) and Insufficient Sleep Syndrome. The assistant also enhanced the
  Excessive Daytime Sleepiness (EDS) scoring with weighted calculations and
  expanded the CSV export functionality to capture all questionnaire data.
  Furthermore, new questions related to pain severity and chronic fatigue were
  incorporated into the questionnaire. The process involved updating data types,
  validation schemas, UI components, and report generation logic for both web
  and PDF formats, ensuring the application now aligns more closely with the
  specified requirements.
